  "title": "Relief Teacher (St. Andrew's Autism Centre)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>·       Plan and deliver engaging lessons tailored to students’ diverse needs. Use evidence-based, autism-friendly teaching strategies and assessments to track students’ progress</p><p>·       Collaborate on curriculum planning and development</p><p>·       Build positive relationships and support individualised education plans (IEPs/ITPs)</p><p>·       Manage behaviours and implement strategies to support students’ well-being</p><p>·       Maintain a safe and positive learning environment</p><p>·       Support co-curricular activities (CCAs) and school initiatives </p><p>·       Participate in work committees to achieve student outcomes</p><p>·       Work with families and external partners to support student development </p><p>·       Assist with transition planning for post-school success </p><p>·       Collaborate with allied professionals to development and implement support plans to support students’ learning and well-being</p><p>·       Maintain and update accurate records, reports and student progress data. When appropriate, provide guidance to junior staff on teaching and learning, and work processes and activities.  <br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p><p>·       Recognised Polytechnic Diploma</p><p>·       Teaching qualifications or equivalent in Special Education will be an advantage</p><p>·        Experience in dealing with children and youths with autism will be an advantage</p>",
